cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MA, cs.SI, cs.DC 

The paper focuses on learning techniques for providing guidance to individuals in the presence of other "learning" individuals in anonymous multi-agent settings. This involves improving the performance of independent reinforcement learners, specifically the popular Deep Q-Networks (DQN) and Advantage Actor Critic (A2C) approaches by exploiting anonymity. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). Additionally, the paper also deals with controlling non-stationarity introduced by other agents using entropy of agent density distribution, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
